default5.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultS
defaultetting the budget and precept is one of my key roles and I am the main decision maker in that process.  
defaultI have a very experienced Chief Finance Officer 
default(
defaultCFO)
default to brief me on the t
defaultechnical detail budget setting
default. 
defaultI have consulted on my draft budget and precept proposals 
defaultwith public, victims and businesses.
default I then work with Surrey Police and my CFO
default to go through the policing priorities, government grant funding
default and the
default results of consultation to develop the budget and precept proposals to put forward to the Police and Crime Panel.
default&#xa0;
default5.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn a climate of increasing austerity, we must make difficult decisions.  I make those decisions in the best interests of the public and in line with the priorities as expressed in the Police and Crime Plan.  
default&#xa0;default5.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI also have an important role in representing the interests of the public of Surrey in the national decisions that impact on our budget and precept. Surrey residents pay the highest precept for their policing in the country, because the county receives one of the lowest levels of Government grant. Other areas with similar crime rates receive as much as double the amount of funding per head of population as Surrey. I will be playing an active role in future discussions on a police funding formula which simply does not reflect the true costs of policing in this country and fails to allocate funding accurately on the basis of need.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
default6.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFrom the very outset
default, I have been
default clear that the priorities of the public should dictate the direction and the style of policing in Surrey. Six ‘People’s Priorities’ form the basis for the Police and Crime Plan for Surrey. I the Chief Constable to account for delivery of and progress against that Plan which I believe will ultimately lead to a reduction in crime, anti-social behaviour and a better police service for local people and victims of crime.  
default&#xa0;
default6.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPCCs are visible and communicate 
defaultin 
defaulta way that Police Authorities were never able to. Recent research 
defaulthas
default demonstrated that over 60% of people have now heard of the PCC role. That compares to 7% who had heard of their Police Author
defaultity. This is a significant step 
defaultforward for local democracy and is something I hope to continue to build on throughout my time in office.
default&#xa0;
default6.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUnlike Police Authorities, engagement, consultation and communication with the public are 
defaultin the DNA of the PCC role
default. I am here to listen to their priorities and make sure they are reflected in the policing services they receive. 
defaultTo illustrate, my activities have included:
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default7.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLike many other police forces, Surrey Police needs to make large savings over the next few years.  
defaultSurrey and Sussex have in the last few years been collaborating on a small number of specialist crime services.  Recently I have agreed with the PCC for Sussex, Katy Bourne, and the two Chief Constables, a vision for future: 
default&#xa0;
default“Surrey and Sussex Police working as one, operationally and organisationally to enhance and improve services for the public whilst reducing costs and responding to local needs”
default&#xa0;
default7.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOn 1 October 2013 Surrey and Sussex have moved towards a lead force model for collaborating in Specialist Crime and Operations with an Assistant Chief Constable in charge of these two commands.   We are currently reviewing Support Service functions to bring these together for the two forces over the next few years.   These changes will help make the savings needed in Surrey and Sussex whilst improving operational resilience.
default&#xa0;
default7.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are also working within Surrey with partners on an Emergency Services Collaboration project
default, encouraging closer working between blue light services
default.  This will be worked up alongside the Surrey/ Sussex collaboration plans. 
default&#xa0;default7.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI, with support from my office, am also taking a national lead role working 
defaultwith other PCCs 
defaulton 
defaultthe provision of victim support services to ensure that the proposed plans to transfer funding and governance of these services to PCC
defaults
default are robust and will deliver the required level of support to victims. 
default&#xa0;default7.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe PCCs in the South East have also signed a deal with BT which will make 20% savings on telecoms over the next 7 years. 
default&#xa0;default7.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe also have a number of other local partnership projects and collaborations that we are working on including the development of Joint Law Enforcement between Surrey Police and Local Councils, a local Surrey Cyber Safe Partnership and taking a lead on Surrey partnership boards. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default8.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI aim to be transparent in the work I do.  I publish all key decisions that I have made along with details of my salary and expenses as well as those for my deputy, assistant commissioner and salaries for all senior staff.   I publish gifts and hospitality, a register of interests and any matters of complaints or conduct. 
